{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/blog/tera-saturday-7-its-a-new-spawn-its-a-new-day","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>Welcome to the return of TeraSaturday, a not-so-weekly update post about all the neat stuff that has been going on in\nthe world of Terasology! Half blog, half changelog, completely cool.</em></p>\n<h2 id=\"-since-last-terasaturday-\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-since-last-terasaturday-\" aria-label=\" since last terasaturday  permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>üì∞ Since last TeraSaturday ...</h2>\n<p>Another week has passed, and we just released <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/releases/tag/v4.1.0-rc.2\">Terasology Alpha 17 (Release Candidate 2)</a> with a bunch of performance bug fixes and performance improvements. We updated the TerasologyLauncher (<a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TerasologyLauncher/releases/tag/v4.2.0\">latest release v4.2.0</a>) so that you can also start the latest release candidates on your Mac üçè.</p>\n<p><em>@DarkWeird</em> tracked down some zombie threads that stopped the game from exiting properly, <em>@Michael P</em> tweaked the lighting code a bit to remove the overexposure in bright daylight, and <em>@Skaldarnar</em> fixed the issue where killing mobs in Josharia's Survival would crash the server.</p>\n<p>Our ... distinctive spawn point features (üôÑ) have been smoothed out by <em>@4D enthusiast</em> who also continued to erase the remnants of the deprecated <code class=\"language-text\">SurfaceHeightFacets</code> from all modules.\n<em>@Niruandaleth</em> applied the finishing touches to the glTF models, unifying our Gooey assests in the <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/MawGooey\">MawGooey module</a> and doing some fine tuning of model sizes.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, new contributors <em>@Paul</em> and <em>@Gwhoyanne</em> fixed the time synchronization between host and clients and now want to add some permissions to our magic time travel keys (<kbd>F3</kbd> to enable debug mode, then do time travel via <kbd>‚Üí</kbd> or <kbd>‚Üê</kbd>).</p>\n<p>In total, that's <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=org%3AMovingBlocks+type%3Apr+merged%3A2020-11-28..2020-12-05\">21 engine RPs</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=org%3ATerasology+type%3Apr+merged%3A2020-11-28..2020-12-05\">40 PRs on modules</a> since November 28.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.083333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/3e828/worldgen.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/e6f2f/worldgen.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/8b983/worldgen.webp 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/b2d4b/worldgen.webp 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/0abaa/worldgen.webp 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/fad48/worldgen.webp 1600w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/7809d/worldgen.jpg 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/4ecad/worldgen.jpg 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/212bf/worldgen.jpg 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/5ef17/worldgen.jpg 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/ac99c/worldgen.jpg 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/b17f8/worldgen.jpg 1600w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/ec3ad9ed4bc50551700d350d84fdcbe3/212bf/worldgen.jpg\"\n            alt=\"World Generation Improvements\"\n            title=\"World Generation Improvements\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"-modulefeature-highlights\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-modulefeature-highlights\" aria-label=\" modulefeature highlights permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>üöÄ Module/Feature Highlights</h2>\n<p>Since we focussed on stabilization and bug fixes this week not much happened regarding gameplay features other than some improvemetns to the in-game help.\n<em>@Niruandaleth</em> and <em>@Skaldarnar</em> did a pass over the in-game help present in Josharia's Survival and worked on some usability aspects.\nItems and Blocks are now sorted by their display name, and the order in which help sections are displayed is now the same all the time.\nIn addition, a few blocks and items got a display name or description added where it was still missing.\nAll this is hopefully just the start of improving the in-game help features offered in our gameplays, making Terasology more accessible for new players üïπ</p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 725px; left:0; width: 100%;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 80.20833333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/3e828/ingame-help.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/e6f2f/ingame-help.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/92338/ingame-help.webp 725w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/8514f/ingame-help.png 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/804b2/ingame-help.png 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/a0209/ingame-help.png 725w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\" type=\"image/png\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/ModuleSite/static/4f9344efb374f4eeb3f8759999d99cbb/a0209/ingame-help.png\" alt=\"Sorted in-game help\" title=\"Sorted in-game help\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n</p>","ti